  "prompt": "Is posting links to your website allowed on Quora?",
  "response": "Yes, posting links to your website on Quora is allowed, but there are some important guidelines and best practices to follow:\n\n1. **Relevance**: The link should be directly relevant to the question or topic being discussed. Posting links that are unrelated or overly promotional is discouraged.\n\n2. **Transparency**: Be transparent about your affiliation with the website. If you're linking to your own site, disclose that it's your site to maintain trust with the community.\n\n3. **Quality Content**: The linked content should be high-quality, informative, and provide value to the reader. Quora discourages linking to spammy or low-quality sites.\n\n4. **No Excessive Promotion**: While sharing links is allowed, excessive self-promotion or spamming links to your website can lead to your posts being flagged, removed, or your account being restricted.\n\n5. **Follow Quora's Policies**: Always adhere to Quora's [Community Guidelines](https://www.quora.com/policy/community_guidelines) and [Terms of Service](https://www.quora.com/about/tos). Violating these rules can result in penalties.\n\n6. **Engage Authentically**: Instead of just dropping links, contribute insightful answers and engage with the community. Adding a link as a supplementary resource can enhance your answer.\n\nBy following these guidelines, you can share links to your website in a way that is helpful and compliant with Quora's rules.",
